20 Aug 2015: Protecting the most vulnerable in Sierra Leone's latest Ebola outbreak
http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/david-bull/sierra-leone-ebola_b_8010444.html
[The 49 households that make up [the village of] Massesebe were under lockdown after a man who had traveled to the village from Freetown for the Eid [a religious holiday at the end of Ramadan fasting] celebrations died of Ebola. This was the 1st Ebola case in Tonkolili District in 5 months. 498 people, including 101 children under 5, were quarantined in the village, and 2 people were confirmed as being Ebola positive.

Because of the vulnerability of newborns, and the concern for well-intentioned people touching the newborn baby and mother after delivery, R and her husband M spoke with a team of UNICEF (United Nations International Children's Emergency Fund) supported psychosocial counselors. The parents agreed that mother and child should move to the nearby Observational Interim Care Center where children are cared for in a child-friendly environment by trained Ebola survivors who do not run the risk of contracting or transmitting the virus. ...more]

Funding
------
19 Aug 2015 Ghana: UN Mission for Ebola Emergency Response supports MoH's Ebola's Response Team
http://allafrica.com/stories/201508200823.html
[The United Nations Mission for Ebola Emergency Response (UNMEER), yesterday [18 Aug 2015] presented 15 vehicles, vehicle spare parts, some office furniture, and some stationary to the Ministry of Health's (MoH's) Ebola Response Team. The vehicles (2 Ford Everest 4x4s, 8 Prado 4x4s, 2 Toyota Hilux Pickups, and 3 Toyota Hiace mini buses), together with the other items, are to help equip the team to be able to fight and completely eradicate the Ebola virus disease (EVD) from the sub-region. ...more]

23 Aug 2015 Sierra Leone: Gold and diamond exports plummet due to Ebola
http://www.ndtv.com/world-news/sierra-leone-gold-and-diamond-exports-plummet-due-to-ebola-1210015
[According to Sierra Leone officials, on Sat [22 Aug 2015], gold exports plunged 3-fold, and diamond exports nearly halved in the 1st half of 2015, a sign of the devastation of the mining industry by the Ebola epidemic. Diamond exports dropped from a high of 64 500 carats in April 2015 to 35 600 carats in July 2015. ...more]

